.TH CNT 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cnt \- count lines, words, and bytes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cnt
.RI [ file ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cnt
counts lines, words, and bytes in each
.IR file .
If no files are given, or if a file is
.BR \- ,
standard input is read.
When multiple files are given a totals line is printed at the end.
Output format per file is:
.PP
.RS
lines  words  bytes  filename
.RE
.PP
This is the JLC equivalent of
.BR wc (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open a file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Count lines/words/bytes in a file:
.EX
cnt README.md
.EE
.TP
Count from stdin:
.EX
echo "hello world" | cnt
.EE
.TP
Count multiple files with totals:
.EX
cnt *.c
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wc (1),
.BR hd (1),
.BR tl (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
